data.enText: a row or layer of sth that has several rows or layers placed one above the other
a wedding cake with three tiers
The seating is arranged in tiers .
one of several levels in an organization or a system

data.chText: 我们额外增加了一层管理。
data.enText: We have introduced an extra tier of administration.

tr: one of two or more layers one atop another
example: tier upon tier of huge casks

tr: something that is used for tying
example: the sail is fastened to the yard with tiers

tr: any one of two or more competitors who tie one another
a relative position or degree of value in a graded group

value.def: A tier is a row or layer of something that has other layers above or below it.

example.ex: ...the auditorium with the tiers of seats around and above it.
example.tran: 四周和上方有一排排座位的礼堂

value.def: A tier is a level in an organization or system.

example.ex: Islanders have campaigned for the abolition of one of the three tiers of municipal power on the island.
example.tran: 岛上居民发起一场运动，要求废除岛上三级市政管理层中的一级。

example.ex: ...the possibility of a two-tier system of universities.
example.tran: 大学实行双重体制的可能性
